Line by Line
When writing Java code, each statement is read by the computer in order, one after the other.

System.out.println("I walked through the door with you");
System.out.println("The air was cold"); 
System.out.println("But something about it felt like home somehow");

The example above would output:

I walked through the door with you
The air was cold
But something about it felt like home somehow

The ln in System.out.println() lets the computer know to print the content and move everything after it to a new line!

This applies to any Java code we write moving forward. 🙌
